def: A neutral; one who professes or practices neutrality. Milman.
The ramus of the lower jaw of a bird as far as it is naked; --commonly used in the plural.
One who vituperates, or censures abusively.
Connection of links or union of parts, as in a chain; a regularor connected series. See Concatenation. Sir T. Browne.
A European lake whitefish (Coregonus Willughbii, or C.Vandesius) native of certain lakes in Scotland and England. It isregarded as a delicate food fish. Called also vendis.
To make slight cracks; to make small, sharp, sudden noises,rapidly or frequently repeated; to crepitate; as, burning thornscrackle.The unknown ice that crackles underneath them. Dryden.
